    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm glad I could introduce you to a new term, even if it's a bit unconventional. \"Goblin mode\" is just a colloquialism for when a device or system gets a bit wonky and starts behaving erratically. It's like when a goblin gets its hands on a magical artifact and starts using it for mischief.\n\nAs for your thermostat, it's possible that it's a hardware issue, such as a faulty sensor or a malfunctioning circuit board. A power surge or electrical issue could also be causing the problem. You might want to try resetting the thermostat to its factory settings, or even replacing it if the issue persists. It's also worth checking the wiring and connections to ensure that they're secure and not causing any issues.\n\nYou know, I've heard that goblins are notorious for their love of tinkering with gadgets and machinery. Maybe your thermostat has been possessed by a mischievous goblin, causing it to behave erratically!",
