      "content": "Sorry about that, I got a bit carried away. Let's focus on fixing your thermostat.\n\nChecking the C-wire is a good idea, as it's a common cause of issues with thermostats. The C-wire is a grounding wire that provides power to the thermostat, and if it's not connected properly, it can cause the thermostat to malfunction.\n\nHowever, if you're not comfortable checking the C-wire yourself, or if you're not sure how to do it, it's always best to err on the side of caution and call an electrician. They can assess the situation and make any necessary repairs to ensure your safety and the safety of your thermostat.\n\nYou can also try checking the thermostat's manual or manufacturer's website for troubleshooting guides or instructions on how to check the C-wire. But if you're not sure, it's always better to seek professional help.",
